Just want to clarify here as I see nearly everyone who has reviewed this watched the Amazon Instant Video version.  I happened to purchase the DVD since i'm a bit of a Dudikoff fan.  I didn't realize until after I had ordered that Amazon lists the language as Castilian.  But it is in fact in English and doesn't even have a Castilian language option. So if your in the states and want to purchase this DVD rest assured it is in English.  This film did not get a NTSC release and probably won't so you will need a region free DVD player that plays PAL DVD's or you can just do what I did,pop it in your pc since there is no region restrictions then hook up to yer tv with hdmi cable to watch it. Hope this helps any Dudikoff completists

This had a good plot.  How it got to the end was as interesting as the end.  Most of the acting was pretty good.  The dialog was OK.  A couple of sex scenes put it out of the family category.  Quite a bit of violence all part of the plot.  The sex scenes were not necessary to the plot.  Some value in showing a little Indian culture.  I enjoyed the story and the presentation was mostly realistic.  The helpful deputy character was not developed enough to make his end actions believable at the time they happened.  The "good guys" were not so good but were honest and dependable.  The evil characters had no good to them.  Some of the other characters were more developed.  It was a fun action movie to watch.  Not great; but worth watching.  I would recommend it.
Passable B movie.  Fun to watch
